\sigma}_R including\ndifferent distributions for each absorption bin, subject to the integral CXB\nconstraint. The distributions observed in many AGN samples can be ruled out by\nour analysis, meaning these samples can not be representative of the full AGN\npopulation. The few samples that fall within the acceptable parameter space are\nhard X-ray-selected, commensurate with their having fewer selection biases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Nov 2019 05:32:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-05"}
