ber 4-6, 2017 CMEs\nwas their arrival at Earth during the phase of maximum Bz amplification. Our\nanalysis highlights how the amplification of the magnetic field of individual\nCMEs in space-time due to interaction processes can be characterised by a\ngrowth, a maximum, and a decay phase, suggesting that the time interval between\nthe CME eruptions and their relative speeds are critical factors in determining\nthe resulting impact of complex CMEs at various heliocentric distances\n(helio-effectiveness).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Nov 2019 10:33:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-04"}
